{{SupportPage|vendor=Linksys|model=E900}} [http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?p=678195 On the DD-WRT forums] (boot log, CFE dump) :"3763-11900102R" is silkscreened on the board ::This is the same '''CyberTAN''' board P/N as the [[Linksys E800]] and the [[Linksys E1200 v2]]. :20:AA:4B OUI Supported by [http://victek.is-a-geek.com/downloads.html RAF] builds of Tomato by Victek. Supported by [http://tomato.groov.pl/download/K26RT-N/ K26RT-N] builds of Tomato by Shibby. Supported by OpenWRT, however as of version 15.05 the wireless radio does not work and pretty much routing is very slow to the point of being unusable. It probably will never be fixed. Do not bother trying. {{TechInfoDepot|Linksys_E900}} The default SSID is probably '''CiscoXXXXX''' where '''XXXXX''' is the last 5 digits of the serial number. If the device has been configured with Cisco Connect the device will probably have a [[Cisco Connect SSIDs|randomly generated SSID]].
